make_unique_and_equip(string sFile)

  An lfun defined for monsters. Clones an unique object into the 
  monster using make_unique_obj and then proceeds to have the monster
  equip the object. See make_unique_obj for more details about 
  unique object cloning.

  Note: Like make_unique_obj, this lfun returns 0 when it cannot
        create a new clone. Useful for cloning non-unique items
        on failure.

  Example: 
           if(!make_unique_and_equip("/obj/uniq_sword"))
             make_and_equip("/obj/regular_sword");


See also: make_unique_obj, make_and_equip, make_limited_and_equip
